                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15285268" author="garydgregory" created="Mon, 16 May 2016 20:50:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In svn trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15286355" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Tue, 17 May 2016 10:14:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The method &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Mac HmacAlgorithms.getInitializedMac(byte[] key)&lt;br/&gt;
is identical to&lt;br/&gt;
Mac HmacAlgorithms.getHmac(byte[] key)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However the former is only used once, so it should probably be the one to be removed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15287770" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Tue, 17 May 2016 22:29:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Dropped the extra method:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;URL: &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc?rev=1744329&amp;amp;view=rev&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc?rev=1744329&amp;amp;view=rev&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Log:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CODEC-218&quot; title=&quot;Refactor HmacUtils methods into the HmacAlgorithms enum&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CODEC-218&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CODEC-218&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; remove unnecessary duplicate method HmacAlgorithms.getInitializedMac&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Modified:&lt;br/&gt;
    commons/proper/codec/trunk/src/main/java/org/apache/commons/codec/digest/HmacAlgorithms.java&lt;br/&gt;
    commons/proper/codec/trunk/src/main/java/org/apache/commons/codec/digest/HmacUtils.java&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15296315" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Mon, 23 May 2016 12:33:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As per the discussions on the dev list, enums are not really suitable here, as the enum cannot support all valid algorithms.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;URL: &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc?rev=1745174&amp;amp;view=rev&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc?rev=1745174&amp;amp;view=rev&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Log:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CODEC-218&quot; title=&quot;Refactor HmacUtils methods into the HmacAlgorithms enum&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CODEC-218&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CODEC-218&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Refactor HmacUtils methods into the HmacAlgorithms enum&lt;br/&gt;
Reverted, because not all algorithms can be supported by the enum&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Modified:&lt;br/&gt;
    commons/proper/codec/trunk/src/changes/changes.xml&lt;br/&gt;
    commons/proper/codec/trunk/src/main/java/org/apache/commons/codec/digest/HmacAlgorithms.java&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The equivalent methods are now available in the HmacUtils class and work for all algorithms, not just the ones in the HmacAlgorithms enum&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
